parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater core can cause the windshield to fog up, reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents. The leakage of antifreeze into the passenger compartment can also pose a health risk to occupants.
symptoms: Strong smell of antifreeze
fogging of windshield
inability to defrost windshield
smoke or vapor coming from vents
leakage of antifreeze onto passenger side floorboard or carpet.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the defroster can cause the windshield to fog up, reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Inability to defrost windshield
fogging of windshield
reduced visibility.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The leakage of antifreeze into the passenger compartment can pose a health risk to occupants.
symptoms: Strong smell of antifreeze
leakage of antifreeze onto passenger side floorboard or carpet.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater core can cause antifreeze to leak into the passenger compartment, leading to reduced visibility due to fogged windows, and potentially causing accidents. The leakage of toxic antifreeze can also pose a health risk to occupants.
symptoms: Antifreeze odor coming from the vents
fogged windows
defroster malfunction
and antifreeze leakage onto the passenger-side floor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent stalling of the engine can cause loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or shuts down intermittently
often when making right turns
and may be accompanied by a smell of burning oil.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The improper venting of the fuel tank can cause detonation problems, leading to explosions that can rock the vehicle, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The car has detonation problems
and the fuel tank has exploded on multiple occasions
causing the vehicle to rock violently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the throttle cable can cause the vehicle to surge forward unexpectedly, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates to accelerate
the accelerator pedal feels stuck or requires additional pressure to overcome
the vehicle lurches forward out of control
the vehicle surges forward when the accelerator pedal is pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent engine malfunction can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to potential accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The "TCL" and "Fix Engine Soon" lights come on while driving
the lights go off when the car is turned off
the lights stay off for several car trips and then come on again intermittently.
